I think that is good idea have a way to include only some icons, for example:

``` scss
$fa-included-icons: (
  glass,
  camera,
  print,
);
@import 'font-awesome/scss/font-awesome';
```

This allows things like:

``` javascript
gulp.task('sass', function () {
  gulp.src('./sass/main.scss')
    .pipe(sass({
      includePaths: [require('font-awesome').scssPath]
    }))
    .pipe(gulp.dest('./build/css'));
});

gulp.task('fonts', function() {
  gulp.src(require('font-awesome').fontPath)
    .pipe(gulp.dest('./build/fonts'));
});
```

Note I only tested this for sass and fonts but added the css and less paths as well.

If anyone wants to use icons without the regular fa classes, but rather applying them to specific elements dynamically.

Example:

```
.upload_button::after {
  @include fa-icon();
  content: fa-icon-var(upload);
}
```

Tested with [node-sass](https://github.com/sass/node-sass) that provides binding for Node.js to [libsass](https://github.com/sass/libsass).

